ints on the formation scenarios. Such information on the occurrence of\nECSNe is important for population synthesis calculations, especially for\nestimating the rate of binary neutron star mergers and resulting\nelectromagnetic and gravitational wave signals. Further progress needs to be\nmade modeling the core collapse process that leads to low-mass neutron stars,\nparticularly in making robust predictions for the mass loss from the progenitor\ncore.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Nov 2016 21:48:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-09"}
