m$0.3 km/s. However, the central group with the\nsame position but at the velocity V$_{LSR}$$\\sim$-3.4 km/s falls on a straight\nline between two high-velocity components detected in 2014. Comparison of the\nlow-velocity positions from 2014 and 1996, based on the same diagram, shows\nthat the majority of the masers maintain their positions near the central\nvelocity V$_{LSR}$=$\\sim$0.3 km/s during the 18 year period.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2016 12:09:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-21"}
