~200), the nozzle\nproducing the cluster jet must provide a large liquid mass fraction at these\nsmall cluster sizes for increasing the harmonic yield. Moreover, cluster jets\nmay allow for quasi-phase matching, as the higher mass of clusters allows for a\nhigher density contrast in spatially structuring the nonlinear medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2016 15:20:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Dec 2016 12:37:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 16 Dec 2016 08:17:16 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 2 May 2017 23:43:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-13"}
